                            <comment id="13257704" author="stack" created="Thu, 19 Apr 2012 19:23:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please explain where the disparity between this.server and this.regions is in in the code Maryann.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13258074" author="maryannxue" created="Fri, 20 Apr 2012 08:11:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In AssignmentManager.unassign(HRegionInfo, boolean)&lt;br/&gt;
            // Remove from the regionsMap&lt;br/&gt;
            synchronized (this.regions) &lt;/p&gt;
{
              this.regions.remove(region);
            }

&lt;p&gt;In AssignmentManager.assign(HRegionInfo, RegionState, boolean, boolean, boolean)&lt;br/&gt;
          synchronized (this.regions) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            this.regions.put(plan.getRegionInfo(), plan.getDestination());
          }

&lt;p&gt;Here, not updating/removing the region from this.servers might cause the balancer to generate incorrect region plans.&lt;br/&gt;
After the fix of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5563&quot; title=&quot;HRegionInfo#compareTo should compare regionId as well&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5563&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-5563&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it seems this problem won&apos;t cause endless loop of wrong balances or a region always in transition.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
